{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Instructions{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-8">
        <p>Your final objective is to create an <strong>Event</strong>. If the participating Teams, Sports Category, Contest and the Location already exist, then you simply click on "Create New Event", pick from the lists of Teams, Locations, Categories, Contests, and enter the Name, Date and Time. To promote the event you can add an image URL (1200 x 600 px recommended) and a note describing the event in a paragraph.</p>
        <p class="p-5"><img src="/assets/instructions/event-creation-process.png" alt="The Process of adding an Event" class="img-fluid"></p>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-8 p-4">
                <h3>
                    List of Sports Events
                </h3>
                <p>
                    Visitors at <a href="http://eventradar-app.herokuapp.com">eventradar-app.herokuapp.com</a> are presented with a list of upcoming events. They can filter the events be category or by date (future or past events). Selecting "Details" presents them with further information about the event including the contact infos of the event's location.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Regular visitors cannot make any changes to the event data, this is reserved to users who have registered and signed in. You can use the guest user user@gmail.com (PW: 123123) to try the admin area yourself.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm m-2" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#eventradar1">
                        Zoom Image
                    </button>
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Modal -->
        <div class="modal fade" id="eventradar1" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="eventradar1" aria-hidden="true">
            <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg">
                <div class="modal-content">
                    <div class="modal-header">
                        <h5 class="modal-title" id="eventradar1">List of Sports Events</h5>
                        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-body">
                        <img src="/assets/instructions/eventradar1.png" class="img-fluid" alt="List of Sports Events">
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-footer">
                        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-8 p-4">
                <h3>
                    Event Details
                </h3>
                <p>
                    Each event has a separate details page showing the marketing slogan, the dates and the teams playing. A longer text is provided with a description. This can be used to describe the circumstances and challenges the participating teams face. If an event is over and the results are entered, then the scores are displayed.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Clicking on the team name shows the team details including the team members. In this example most teams only contain placeholder data, only Rapid Wien, FC Bayern MÃ¼nchen and Sturm Graz feature real team information and player data.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm m-2" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#eventradar2">
                        Zoom Image
                    </button>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 text-center py-4">
                <img src="/assets/instructions/eventradar2.png" alt="Event Details" class="img-fluid" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#eventradar2">
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Modal -->
        <div class="modal fade" id="eventradar2" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="eventradar2" aria-hidden="true">
            <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg">
                <div class="modal-content">
                    <div class="modal-header">
                        <h5 class="modal-title" id="eventradar2">Event Details</h5>
                        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-body">
                        <img src="/assets/instructions/eventradar2.png" class="img-fluid" alt="Event Details">
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-footer">
                        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-4 text-center py-4">
                <img src="/assets/instructions/eventradar3.png" alt="Editing Content" class="img-fluid" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#eventradar3">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-8 p-4">
                <h3>
                    Editing Content
                </h3>
                <p>
                    When a user is logged in they can click on the 'Admin' menu in the top right corner of the navigation. The menu lists all the available views. These include <strong>events</strong>, <strong>locations</strong>, <strong>teams</strong>, <strong>persons</strong> (team members), <strong>roles</strong>, <strong>leagues</strong>, <strong>contests</strong>, <strong>sports categories</strong>, and <strong>countries</strong>. They can access the <strong>instructions</strong>, for more information on how to make changes.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm m-2" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#eventradar3">
                        Zoom Image
                    </button>
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Modal -->
        <div class="modal fade" id="eventradar3" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="eventradar3" aria-hidden="true" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#eventradar3">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-primary" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#eventradar3">
                Zoom
            </button>
            <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg">
                <div class="modal-content">
                    <div class="modal-header">
                        <h5 class="modal-title" id="eventradar3">Editing Content</h5>
                        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-body">
                        <img src="/assets/instructions/eventradar3.png" class="img-fluid" alt="EventRadar">
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-footer">
                        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
            <p><img src="/assets/instructions/eventradar-overview.png" alt="EventRadar Overview" class="img-fluid"></p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h3>Detailed Breakdown</h3>
        <p>Please find a more detailed breakdown of each data type below.</p>

        <h4>Events</h4>
        <p>Before you add your Event, make sure you have at least two Teams, a Location, a Contest and a Sports Category.Then enter the Name, Date and Time. You need an Image URL and Notes to promote the Event.</p>
        <p><img src="/assets/instructions/event-form.png" alt="The form for creating an event" class="img-fluid border rounded mb-4"></p>

        <h4>Locations</h4>
        <p>Before adding a Location, make sure that the Country you need for the Location has been added. Then enter the Name, Image URL (300 x 200px recommended), Audience Capacity, Website, Phone Number, Address Information, and Description.</p>
        <p><img src="/assets/instructions/location-form.png" alt="The form for adding a location" class="img-fluid border rounded mb-4"></p>

        <h4>Teams</h4>
        <p>Creating new Teams requires the most work. You need a League, a Country, a Sports Category and a logo (180 x 180px or a similar square aspect ratio recommended). Having Team Members (Persons) is not mandatory but advised. Adding persons requires the right role to exist.</p>
        <p><img src="/assets/instructions/team-form.png" alt="The form for adding a new team" class="img-fluid border rounded mb-4"></p>

        <h4>Persons</h4>
        <p>The only prerequisite for adding a person is that the respective Team and Role already exist. Then it is only a matter of entering the names and the photo URL (220 x 290px or a resolution with this aspect ratio recommended). Please note that if you do not include an image URL, then a placeholder will automatically be used. </p>
        <p><img src="/assets/instructions/person-form.png" alt="The form for adding a new person" class="img-fluid border rounded mb-4"></p>

        <h4>Roles</h4>
        <p>At present there are four roles that can be assigned to a Person: "Trainer (Coach)", "Player", "Team Captain" and "Doctor". You can add a new role and enter a name for it. It will then be automatically available when adding new persons or editing existing ones.</p>
        <p><img src="/assets/instructions/role-form.png" alt="The form for adding a new role" class="img-fluid border rounded mb-4"></p>

        <h4>Leagues and Contests</h4>
        <p>Leagues and contests are very similar. Leagues are needed for Teams and Contests are required for Events. You can add new leagues/contests and edit existing ones. Both need you to enter a name, a logo URL and a website URL. Leagues need you to select a country. Contests need you to enter a federation name. If you do not provide a logo, then a placeholder will be used instead.</p>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <p><img src="/assets/instructions/league-form.png" alt="The form for adding a new league" class="img-fluid border rounded mb-4"></p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <p><img src="/assets/instructions/contest-form.png" alt="The form for adding a new contest" class="img-fluid border rounded mb-4"></p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h4>Sports Categories</h4>
        <p>Adding a new sports category is easy. It only requires the name of the category and - if necessary - an alias (e.g. the alias for "Football" is "Soccer"). New categories are automatically included in the menu on the event page. There is also the option to add a description of the sport. At the moment this is only displayed for the admin in the Category page and is not shown to public visitos.</p>
        <p><img src="/assets/instructions/category-form.png" alt="The form for adding a new category" class="img-fluid border rounded mb-4"></p>

        <h4>Countries</h4>
        <p>Currently 195 countries and their flags are included by default. It is very likely that all the countries you will ever need are already in the list and you will not have to add a new country for years to come. Countries only require a Name and a Flag URL (approx. 200 x 120px recommended).</p>
        <p><img src="/assets/instructions/country-form.png" alt="The form for adding a new country" class="img-fluid border rounded mb-4"></p>
    </div>
